ptex
------------------------------------------
Ptex is a texture mapping system developed by Walt Disney Animation Studios
for production-quality rendering:

 * No UV assignment is required! Ptex applies a separate texture to each face
   of a subdivision or polygon mesh.
 * The Ptex file format can efficiently store hundreds of thousands of texture
   images in a single file.
 * The Ptex API provides cached file I/O and high-quality filtering -
   everything that is needed to easily add Ptex support to a
   production-quality renderer or texture authoring application.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.6.1-1
  libgcc1-5.4.0-1
  libPtex0-2.1.28-1bl1
  libstdc++6-5.4.0-1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1
  zlib0-1.2.8-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-4
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.23.0-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-5.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-1
  python-2.7.12-1

Canonical website:
  http://ptex.us/

Canonical download:
  http://github.com/wdas/ptex/archive/v2.1.28.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ptex-2.1.28-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ptex-2.1.28-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ptex-2.1.28-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ptex-2.1.28-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libPtex0-2.1.28-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libPtex-devel-2.1.28-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ptex)
  /usr/bin/ptxinfo.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ptex.README
  /usr/share/doc/ptex/README
  /usr/share/doc/ptex/html/FilterFootprint.html
  /usr/share/doc/ptex/html/uvellipse.png

(libPtex0)
  /usr/bin/cygPtex-0.dll

(libPtex-devel)
  /usr/include/PtexHalf.h
  /usr/include/PtexInt.h
  /usr/include/PtexUtils.h
  /usr/include/PtexVersion.h
  /usr/include/Ptexture.h
  /usr/lib/libPtex.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/ptex.pc

